cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper proposes a new approach to detecting out-of-distribution data in deep neural networks using a Bayesian variational autoencoder model. The paper focuses on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses computer vision datasets to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also uses stochastic gradient Markov chain Monte Carlo, which is a common technique in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses information-theoretic measures, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SD (Sound) sub-category.
